&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Re:Build Manufacturing – New Kensington&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re:Build Manufacturing New Kensington is part of the Re:Build family of companies, located in New Kensington, PA. Capabilities in a wide variety of industries and materials allow our unique value proposition to bring exciting and advanced programs back to American Manufacturing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re:Build Manufacturing is a rapidly growing family of industrial businesses combining enabling technologies, operational superiority, and strategic M&amp;amp;A to build America&#39;s next generation industrial company. At Re:Build we deploy deep expertise in operations management and technology to supercharge performance of our subsidiaries by implementing core technologies across industrial platforms in diverse growth markets. Our goal is to help revitalize the U.S. manufacturing base over the coming decades, creating substantial opportunities for our employees and the communities where we operate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We leverage deep professional expertise and a candid, principled operating culture to drive differentiated outcomes for our customers, our employees, our communities and our investors. Ours is a fast-paced environment where individuals can stretch and be challenged with a wide variety of opportunities and projects. We empower and support our employees to pursue their fullest potential and provide meaningful avenues for personal and professional growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently searching for CNC Machinists to join our team at our newly renovated plant in New Kensington, PA. As a CNC Machinist, you will be running state of the art CNC machines manufactured by DN solutions, DMG Mori, and Haas to help us serve customers in many industries including aerospace, defense, and medical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in precision CNC machining of a variety of materials (i.e. metals, alloys, plastics, composites, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Milling: 3-axis required, 3+2, 4-axis horizontal and 5-axis preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turning: Mill-turn experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apprenticeship or associate’s degree preferred, but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret drawings, BOM&#39;s and work instructions/aids&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mathematical/Technical understanding of basic math, including algebra and geometry, decimals, fractions, measurements (and measuring tools), etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you get to do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform CNC Operations, to include machine set-up, fixturing, tool building and running for turning and 3 and 5 axis vertical and horizontal milling capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Machines components to the prescribed tolerances based on information such as: provided drawings, BOM’s, work instructions, and safety procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows all applicable Quality Management System procedures, work instructions, and forms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows process routing document. Performs inspection(s) and legibly records results where required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs daily preventative maintenance on equipment and cleans work area after each shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tools and Platforms&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DMG Mori DMU-FD125 Duo-Block&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-axis mill/turn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12,000rpm spindle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DN Solutions DVF-500&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-axis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;18,000rpm spindle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;120/90 pocket tool changer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Haas UMC-750SS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-axis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12,000rpm spindle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50 tool carousel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&g

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Re:Build Manufacturing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re:Build Manufacturing is a growing family of industrial and engineering businesses combining enabling technologies, operational superiority, and strategic M&amp;amp;A to build America’s next generation industrial company. At Re:Build we deploy deep expertise in engineering, operations management, and technology to supercharge the performance of our member companies. We leverage deep professional expertise and a candid, principled operating culture to drive differentiated outcomes. Ours is a fast-paced environment where individuals can stretch and be challenged to pursue their fullest potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re:Build was founded to pioneer a profitable model for the revitalization of US manufacturing. We’ve assembled a powerful set of complimentary capabilities and lines of business that enable us to pursue a wide range of end markets. Our acquired businesses are grounded in build-to-print and by-the-hour engineering and design services, and we’re leveraging their combined expertise to migrate to increasingly sophisticated program development and production, as well as the generation of our own products. Our unique set of capabilities lend themselves to highly complex systems and products, and we offer customers a range of services including product and systems design, automation, fabrication, assembly, and large volume contract manufacturing. Our customers span a wide array of industries including aerospace, defense, mobility, healthcare, pharma, biotech, clean tech, chemicals, energy, lifestyle, food production, and industrial equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly capable and adaptable Accounting Manager to lead financial operations across various early-stage business units with their own unique business models spanning AI-powered software, SaaS and technology services, hardware/drone technology, and manufacturing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of technical accounting rigor and startup operational agility. You&#39;ll be managing the financial complexities of multiple businesses simultaneously- each at different stages of maturity, with different revenue models, cost structures, and reporting needs. You&#39;ll need to bring order to ambiguity while maintaining the flexibility these emerging businesses require.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate thrives in dynamic, fast-paced environments where &quot;building the plane while flying it&quot; is the norm. You&#39;re energized by the challenge of establishing scalable financial processes and controls across diverse business models - from software subscription revenue to product sales to service delivery- while each business unit is still defining its go-to-market strategy and scaling operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Accounting Manager will serve as the day-to-day financial steward, ensuring accurate and timely reporting, strong internal controls, and compliance with applicable accounting standards across jurisdictions. This is a high-impact, high-visibility role with significant opportunity for professional growth as the company scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you get to do!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple business units with a focus on process improvement and infrastructure build-out to driving efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all aspects of accounting (accounts receivable, accounts payable, and cash activities) ensuring compliance with GAAP and internal controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the monthly financial close process, including intercompany transactions, reconciliations, journal entry review, and variance analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invoice customers and execute revenue recognition in accordance with ASC 606 principles across diverse revenue streams, including SaaS, professional services, and physical product

