&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an assembler, you must have an interest in mechanics and the ability to notice and address small details. An outstanding assembler should comprehend and follow detailed verbal and written instructions, as well as diagrams, blueprints, and other technical documents, and be a great teammate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you get to do!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Perform a variety of production and manufacturing processes, such as staging production assembly parts and manually installing key tops, switches, levers, and wires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Operate various production assembly machines and use hand tools to make, repair, and assemble parts and products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Read and interpret technical documents, including basic engineering drawings, specifications, bills of material, schematics, blueprints, operating procedures, and other verbal or written instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Exercise responsibility for the quantity and quality of parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Visually inspect parts to standards, identify defective or flawed items, handle them according to established procedures, and return flawed products to Production for reworking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Work with other members of the line or group to assemble products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;Pack finished product.&lt;/li&gt;
